  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into quarters lengthways, then into thin slices</p>\r\n<p>Slice the<strong> courgettes</strong>&nbsp;thinly</p>\r\n<p>Add the sliced <strong>aubergine</strong> and <strong>courgette</strong> to a baking tray season generously with&nbsp;<strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong>, drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and&nbsp;a pinch&nbsp;of the <strong>oregano</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;</strong>then<strong>&nbsp;</strong>pop in the&nbsp;oven until step 6&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/greek-vegetable-bake/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>tomatoes</strong> into wedges&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> tomatoes</strong> with a pinch of both&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and cook them for 3 min or until beginning to soften</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/greek-vegetable-bake/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> cinnamon</strong> and 2/3 of the <strong>garlic </strong>to the tomato pan and cook for a further min, then add the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, the remaining <strong>oregano</strong> and a small drizzle of the <strong>vinegar</strong> and stir until combined</p>\r\n<p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> and cook for 5-7 min or until thickened to the consistency of a pasta sauce</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/greek-vegetable-bake/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>tomato sauce</strong> to a bowl, wipe the pan clean and return it to a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Add 40g <span class=\"text-danger\">[80g]</span> <strong>butter</strong>&nbsp;to the pan</p>\r\n<p>Once melted, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon for 1 min, until combined</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/greek-vegetable-bake/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and whisk into a smooth sauce, then add the&nbsp;bay <strong>leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span></strong>,&nbsp;remaining <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 3-5 min until thickened&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, grate the <strong>cheese</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once the sauce has thickened, remove it from the heat and add most of the cheese</p>\r\n<p>Season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and&nbsp;remove the <strong>bay leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span>&nbsp;</strong>- this is your <strong>b</strong><strong>&eacute;chamel sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/greek-vegetable-bake/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove&nbsp;the <strong>aubergine</strong> and <strong>courgettte</strong> from the oven and <strong>combine&nbsp;</strong>with the <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the vegetables to an <strong>oven proof dish</strong> (or individual ones) and pat them down into a layer&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Top with the <strong>b&eacute;chemal</strong> and scatter the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and remaining <strong>cheese</strong>&nbsp;over the top&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/greek-vegetable-bake/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the bake in the oven for 10-15 min or until golden on top and bubbling</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, combine the mustard and remaining <strong>vinegar</strong>&nbsp;with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper&nbsp;</strong>- this is your dressing&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/greek-vegetable-bake/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dress the salad once the bake is cooked and serve to the side</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
